---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AdSlot from '../components/common/AdSlot.astro';

const dmcaSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  'name': 'DMCA Policy - Text to Handwriting',
  'description': 'Review our Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA) compliance policies and infringement claims submission details.'
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="DMCA Copyright Policy - Text to Handwriting"
  description="DMCA policy page for Text to Handwriting. Learn how to submit copyright infringement notices and claims details."
  activeTab="dmca"
  schema={dmcaSchema}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8">
    <AdSlot slotId="header-leaderboard" />

    <div class="border-b border-hairline pb-4 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-primary uppercase font-mono">DMCA Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-mute font-mono mt-1">Digital Millennium Copyright Act Compliance Policy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-xs md:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        **Text to Handwriting** respects the intellectual property rights of others and expects users of our platform to do the same. In accordance with the Digital Millennium Copyright Act of 1998 (DMCA), we will respond promptly to claims of copyright infringement committed on our website.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">1. Client-Side Infrastructure Note</h2>
      <p>
        Before filing an infringement notice, please note that **our platform does not host, store, or publish user-generated content on our databases**. All text-to-handwriting conversions, document compilations, signature generation, and file exports occur **client-side directly inside the user's local web browser**. We do not have database access to delete or retrieve any documents, cursive notes, or images generated by individual visitors.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">2. How to File an Infringement Claim</h2>
      <p>
        If you are a copyright owner or an authorized agent thereof, and believe that any content hosted on our site (such as user interface assets, specific fonts, templates, or branding elements) infringes upon your copyright, you may submit a formal notification containing the following:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li>A physical or electronic signature of a person authorized to act on behalf of the owner of the infringed copyright.</li>
        <li>Identification of the copyrighted work claimed to have been infringed (e.g., specific images, CSS styling, or font properties).</li>
        <li>Identification of the material that is claimed to be infringing and information sufficient to permit us to locate the material (the specific page URL).</li>
        <li>Your contact details, including your address, telephone number, and email address.</li>
        <li>A statement that you have a good faith belief that use of the material in the manner complained of is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law.</li>
        <li>A statement that the information in the notification is accurate, and under penalty of perjury, that you are authorized to act on behalf of the owner of an exclusive right that is allegedly infringed.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">3. Where to Submit Claims</h2>
      <p>
        All DMCA notices must be sent to our designated Copyright Agent via email:
        <br />
        <strong>Email:</strong> <code>dmca@texttohandwriting.me</code>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">4. Counter-Notification Procedure</h2>
      <p>
        If you believe that the material removed (or to which access was disabled) is not infringing, or that you have authorization from the copyright owner, you may send a counter-notification to the Copyright Agent containing:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li>Your physical or electronic signature.</li>
        <li>Identification of the material that has been removed or to which access has been disabled and the location prior to removal.</li>
        <li>A statement under penalty of perjury that you have a good faith belief that the material was removed or disabled as a result of mistake or misidentification.</li>
        <li>Your name, address, telephone number, and email address, along with a statement that you consent to jurisdiction of the courts.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <AdSlot slotId="footer-leaderboard" />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
